name: VOLARE LUX
description:
Kingdom: Animalia
Family: Cruentus
Genus: Volare
Species: Lux

The Volare Lux or Starlight Mosquito are nocturnal insects, they spend the morning until evening sleeping and then use the night to roam and hunt for food. Starlight Mosquito live in groups and travel over places at night.

This insects belong to the blood-sucker insect class. The tentacles around their mouth can detect the smell of blood, thus enabling the insect to hunt at night.

The chemical reactions on their body allow them to produce a light just like color-changing lamps that used for communication tool, as a colony of Starlight Mosquito explores through the night, these swarms will appear like hundreds of stars moving beautifully but thirsty for blood.
